article_title: State wants Little Egg Harbor to list homes abandoned after Sandy
article_text: We have used your information to see if you have a subscription with us. So far we have not found one. If you feel you are currently subscribed please click on the button to attempt to find your account.

og.description: LITTLE EGG HARBOR TOWNSHIP — Township officials have repeatedly said that 5,000 homes in this southern Ocean County community were substantially damaged by Hurricane Sandy, but the township has yet to conduct a survey to determine how many of those properties have been abandoned.
